9: I'll indulge you as you indulge me...
13:
Whoa, what's going on? Is this
another event?
17:
Er, no. We were on our way back
from one when we stopped here.
19:
Yugiri-san decided to perform for a
bit, as thanks for the food, and
before we knew it...
22:
So this was just a casual, free show?
No advertising or anything? Wow!
28:
I'll take your astonishment as a
compliment.
30: Are you two here for food?
34:
No, we were just passing by when
we heard you singing, so we peeked
in.
37: Devoted fans, are we? I'm flattered.
40:
I can't think of anyone who
WOULDN'T be a fan! Isn't she so
much fun to talk to?
41:
And that's on top of being a pretty
lass with a heckuva voice! Can't
believe I was lucky enough to meet
her today!
44:
*giggle* Flattery will get you
nowhere, I'm afraid.
46:
Why don't you sit down and order
more food? The owner of this
establishment was gracious enough
to let me sing here, after all.
49:
Haha, that I can definitely do! 'Scuse
me, I'd like to order!
52:
Alk. Light. You should eat as well.
Does the recommended menu suit
your tastes?
55: Oh, yeah, sure. Sounds good to me.
58:
I have to hand it to you, Number 5.
Business is booming thanks to you!
59:
Would ya consider stopping by
more often?
61:
As much as I'd like to... I do have my
idol work with Franchouchou.
64:
My schedule would depend entirely
on how well my activities are going
there...
70:
Is that all? How about I help you out
then?
72:
Just promise you'll drop by with a
performance every so often!
75:
You want to become a sponsor?
Truly?
77:
Excellent. If you could work out the
details with my manager,
Kotaro-han, that would be great.
80:
You got it.
Business is gonna go through the
roof, I just know it!
84:
Talk about hook, line, and sinker...
That was impressive.
87:
I totally had no idea where you were
going with that.
93:
You'll have to forgive the slight lie, of
course.
95:
But this way, we'll get more job
offers, and he'll have more
customers. Everyone wins.
100:
You know, you've adjusted to this
world quite quickly. Much faster
than your friends...
102:
To the point where it almost seems
like you have no desire to return to
your own.
107:
Rather than having no desire, I'd say
that I'm simply comfortable
wherever I go.
110:
This is my second time waking up in
an unfamiliar setting, after all.
115:
Yeah, Yugiri-san was alive during a
time period way before ours.
117:
Even if we made it back, the world
she lived in is already long gone...
121: ...My apologies. I spoke out of line.
125:
It's all right, I never minded the fact.
Life is enjoyable as it is right now.
127:
There's always something new to
see and learn.
133:
By the way... About your behavior
and choice of clothing...
137:
I'm a little concerned that you might
draw unwanted attention as you are
now...
142:
Do you think me naive and
defenseless, Light?
146:
N-no, that's not what I meant! I'm
only worried—
149:
Sakura-han. Alk. My ears didn't
deceive me, did they?
155:
Yugiri-san, you should cut him some
slack. He looks like he's about to cry.
160:
Eh, Light's totally in the wrong here
though.
170:
It seems I have to teach someone
here a little lesson.
175:
U-um, I... I am extremely sorry for my
transgression...
178:
Why don't you come closer and
show me how sorry you truly are?
184: Wh-what do I do now?! Save me, Alk!
